Introduction

Tomorrow X Together (TXT) is a South Korean boy group under Big Hit Entertainment. The group, read as "Tomorrow by Together," consists of five members: Yeonjun, Soobin, Beomgyu, Taehyun, and Huening Kai.

TXT debuted on March 4, 2019, with the EP The Dream Chapter: Star, which reached No. 140 on the Billboard 200, making them the first 4th generation Kpop group to chart on the ranking. On January 15, 2020, they made their Japanese debut with the single Magic Hour, which topped the Oricon Daily Chart and peaked at No. 2 on the Oricon Weekly Singles Chart.

Their 2021 album The Chaos Chapter: Freeze received widespread acclaim, earning a Metascore of 89 on Metacritic, making TXT the only 4th generation act and the fastest Korean artist to debut an album on the platform. In 2023, they became the first Kpop group to headline Lollapalooza, and on June 3, 2024, they became the first Kpop group to sell out two shows at Madison Square Garden.

On December 10, 2024, Big Hit Music announced that TXT would take an extended break to spend time with their families and recharge.
